\n	xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\"\n	xmlns:atom=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\"\n	xmlns:sy=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\"\n	xmlns:slash=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\"\n	>\n\n<channel>\n	<title>Blog &#8211; Timely</title>\n	<atom:link href=\"https://time.ly/blog/feed/\" rel=\"self\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" />\n	<link>https://time.ly</link>\n	<description>Website Calendar by Timely</description>\n	<lastBuildDate>Tue, 07 Feb 2017 20:45:51 +0000</lastBuildDate>\n	<language>en-US</language>\n	<sy:updatePeriod>hourly</sy:updatePeriod>\n	<sy:updateFrequency>1</sy:updateFrequency>\n	\n	<item>\n		<title>How Hubs Can Leverage Free Beta Calendars</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/hubs-can-leverage-free-beta-calendars/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 01 Feb 2017 14:20:21 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323100</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Allow members in your community to send events to your site directly from their own calendar by using our free beta calendar. They can click here to sign up! Event contributors do not even need a website! They can manage their events from our web application (though most would embed their new calendar on their website if they<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/hubs-can-leverage-free-beta-calendars/\" title=\"ReadHow Hubs Can Leverage Free Beta Calendars\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/hubs-can-leverage-free-beta-calendars/\">How Hubs Can Leverage Free Beta Calendars</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Finding Events In Your Area &#8211; Community Hubs</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/finding-events-area-community-hubs/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 18 Jan 2017 19:52:12 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323057</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>You have an amazing looking calendar which is great! What are some ways in which you can keep your calendar relevant and full? 1. Pulling in feeds Save yourself some time with automation. You can pull in feeds from other calendars, the feeds are updated hourly which will ensure your calendar stays up to date<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/finding-events-area-community-hubs/\" title=\"ReadFinding Events In Your Area &#8211; Community Hubs\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/finding-events-area-community-hubs/\">Finding Events In Your Area &#8211; Community Hubs</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>I have a Core Calendar But I Am Looking For More</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/core-calendar-looking/</link>\n		<pubDate>Mon, 09 Jan 2017 21:57:26 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323038</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>You have the Timely Core calendar and you are looking for a little bit more? With the Core+ you will have 5 additional great add-ons which will help you continue to create a beautiful calendar. Extended Views: create a more visually appealing calendar which will help attract visitors to your site with the Posterboard and<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/core-calendar-looking/\" title=\"ReadI have a Core Calendar But I Am Looking For More\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/core-calendar-looking/\">I have a Core Calendar But I Am Looking For More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Keeping School&#8217;s Connected</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/keeping-schools-connected/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 14 Dec 2016 19:44:52 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322920</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Using Time.ly gives schools an easy way of promoting their events out to the community, parents, teachers and students. Paper Newsletters often don&#8217;t make it home or get thrown out. Why not have a connected calendar to simplify the process? In turn, parents will not have to worry about missing their kids school events again.<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/keeping-schools-connected/\" title=\"ReadKeeping School&#8217;s Connected\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/keeping-schools-connected/\">Keeping School&#8217;s Connected</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Solving Common Headaches of Tourism Sites &#8211; Hub Calendar</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/solving-common-headaches-tourism-sites-hub-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 07 Dec 2016 16:13:18 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322912</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We have seen some common problems among tourism sites. So we have introduced features to help with these struggles in our Hub calendar including: Filling your calendar full of events via importing feed functions Reducing your time/expenses with automation Increasing revenue with EventPromote Promoting major events over smaller community events with Featured status Allowing your<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/solving-common-headaches-tourism-sites-hub-calendar/\" title=\"ReadSolving Common Headaches of Tourism Sites &#8211; Hub Calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/solving-common-headaches-tourism-sites-hub-calendar/\">Solving Common Headaches of Tourism Sites &#8211; Hub Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Make Your Calendar Flow Nicely With Proper Organization</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/make-calendar-flow-proper-organization/</link>\n		<pubDate>Mon, 21 Nov 2016 21:30:35 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322872</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Make your calendar flow nicely. Create categories, tags &#38; filters.  There are a lot of events happening around you. How you categories these events sends a strong message as to what events are available and what events you find important. Additionally, categories, tags and filters help to keep your calendar organized and help people to<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/make-calendar-flow-proper-organization/\" title=\"ReadMake Your Calendar Flow Nicely With Proper Organization\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/make-calendar-flow-proper-organization/\">Make Your Calendar Flow Nicely With Proper Organization</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Allow Others To Post Onto Your Calendar Using Front End Submissions</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/allow-others-post-onto-calendar-using-front-end-submissions/</link>\n		<pubDate>Mon, 07 Nov 2016 21:12:01 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322848</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>You can allow other members in your community to post events to your calendar by enabling the front end submissions feature. You have the option to approve posts before they go live on your calendar, or if you are in a very trusting community then you can have the posts publish automatically. For Hub users<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/allow-others-post-onto-calendar-using-front-end-submissions/\" title=\"ReadAllow Others To Post Onto Your Calendar Using Front End Submissions\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/allow-others-post-onto-calendar-using-front-end-submissions/\">Allow Others To Post Onto Your Calendar Using Front End Submissions</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Automate Your Newsletters Using MailChimp</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/automate-newsletters-using-mailchimp/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 28 Oct 2016 14:06:54 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322809</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Time.ly Hub calendars have a basic integration with MailChimp designed to make your life easier! You can automate the process of sending out weekly event newsletters and event notifications. Additionally, you can use the Single Mail feature to send out custom email newsletters or notifications to specific subscribers. Use Mailchimp to continue to grow your<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/automate-newsletters-using-mailchimp/\" title=\"ReadAutomate Your Newsletters Using MailChimp\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/automate-newsletters-using-mailchimp/\">Automate Your Newsletters Using MailChimp</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Featured Events (Hub Calendar)</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/featured-events-hub-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 21 Oct 2016 19:34:39 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322792</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Are you looking to highlight events in your calendar? Featured Events is a great way to highlight the events you would like to stand out in your calendar. Additionally, Featured Events can be used with EventPromote to monetize your calendar by selling featured listings! Continue to make you calendar stand out by adding Featured Events.<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/featured-events-hub-calendar/\" title=\"ReadFeatured Events (Hub Calendar)\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/featured-events-hub-calendar/\">Featured Events (Hub Calendar)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Monetize Your Calendar With EventPromote!</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/monetize-calendar-eventpromote/</link>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Oct 2016 18:52:38 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322712</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Are you looking for a way to monetize your calendar? EventPromote is off and running! You can now have the ability to collect money via your frontend (post your event) button. You could charge for featured status, allow images, show their ticketing/registration link, or any other promotional/sponsorship packages you want to make available. People are most likely to<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/monetize-calendar-eventpromote/\" title=\"ReadMonetize Your Calendar With EventPromote!\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/monetize-calendar-eventpromote/\">Monetize Your Calendar With EventPromote!</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Changes AIOEC 2.5.9 and add-ons</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/changes-aioec-2-5-9-and-add-ons/</link>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 11 Aug 2016 20:34:33 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[2.3.9]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[cost]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[free event]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[tickets]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[timezone]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322243</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Hello friends, We just released AIOEC 2.3.9 for both Timely hosted users and for WP.org as well as some updates to few add-ons. Two significant updates are: We had the “Free” box automatically checked for &#8220;Cost and tickets&#8221; section when creating an event, as most users create Free events. Today&#8217;s change is that we&#8217;ll no longer have it selected by<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/changes-aioec-2-5-9-and-add-ons/\" title=\"ReadChanges AIOEC 2.5.9 and add-ons\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/changes-aioec-2-5-9-and-add-ons/\">Changes AIOEC 2.5.9 and add-ons</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Timely network becomes a reality in version 2.5</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/timely-network-becomes-a-reality-in-version-2-5/</link>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 21:28:45 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[aristotel]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Basic Features]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[API]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[ICS import]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[import feeds]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=322213</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>In the 2.5 release we did a major strategic change supporting the expansion of our product beyond the prior  WordPress plugin by creating an independent web application that serves our plugin  via Timely’s API. The change was to replace the local import of ICS feeds with an API engine. Building a web application served by<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/timely-network-becomes-a-reality-in-version-2-5/\" title=\"ReadTimely network becomes a reality in version 2.5\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/timely-network-becomes-a-reality-in-version-2-5/\">Timely network becomes a reality in version 2.5</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>2.3.6</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/2-3-6/</link>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Feb 2016 04:00:36 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Release Notes]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=321421</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/2-3-6/\">2.3.6</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>2.3.5 Released</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/2-3-5-released/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Jan 2016 17:58:58 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Release Notes]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=321396</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Release Notes for 2.3.5 For All users: &#8211; Import ICS compatibility with WordPress 4.4 &#8211; Event location details corrected where Google maps pin marked the wrong location &#8211; When an event with ticket is exported via an ICS feed, the description will include the &#8220;Buy ticket URL&#8221; to help event seekers purchase a ticket for<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/2-3-5-released/\" title=\"Read2.3.5 Released\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/2-3-5-released/\">2.3.5 Released</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Beta testers wanted for our new ticketing feature</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/</link>\n		<pubDate>Mon, 28 Sep 2015 21:53:53 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Releases]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=320846</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>UPDATE: Timely ticketing is now available to all users! Do you have relatively simple ticketing/registration needs? Do you have better things to do than double event entry? Would you rather save money on your ticketing transactions? We&#8217;re looking for 25 beta testers who want to kick around an integrated ticketing solutions for Timely calendar users.  Rather<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/\" title=\"ReadBeta testers wanted for our new ticketing feature\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/ticketing-add-on-beta-testers-wanted/\">Beta testers wanted for our new ticketing feature</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Top 10 How-to Videos for your Timely calendar</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/</link>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 06 Aug 2015 02:56:30 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Bradley Roulston]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Pre Sale Questions]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Getting Started]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Basic Features]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Additional Features]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Tips and Tricks]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Troubleshooting]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Featured Events]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Calendar Insights]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Tutorials]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[video]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[youtube]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://time.ly/?p=317457</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Want the most from your Timely calendar? Check out our new Timely Tube YouTube Channel. Our current playlists include a How-to Video Series for WordPress plugin users, Hubs, and a playlist of videos by Timely Users. Check it out at https://www.youtube.com/user/TimelyTube/playlists. These videos will walk you through how to install/embed and use all your Timely tools. They&#8217;ll teach you how to make your Timely calendar<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/\" title=\"ReadTop 10 How-to Videos for your Timely calendar\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/top-10-how-to-videos-for-your-timely-calendar/\">Top 10 How-to Videos for your Timely calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n	</channel>\n</rss>\n\";s:7:\"timeout\";i:10;s:15:\"force_fsockopen\";b:0;s:10:\"force_feed\";b:0;s:5:\"cache\";b:1;s:14:\"cache_duration\";i:3600;s:28:\"autodiscovery_cache_duration\";i:604800;s:14:\"cache_location\";s:7