/p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/solving-common-problems-community-hubs-hub-calendar/\">Solving Common Problems For Community Hubs &#8211; Hub Calendar</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>How Hubs Can Leverage Free Beta Calendars</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/hubs-can-leverage-free-beta-calendars/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 01 Feb 2017 14:20:21 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323100</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>Allow members in your community to send events to your site directly from their own calendar by using our free beta calendar. They can click here to sign up! Event contributors do not even need a website! They can manage their events from our web application (though most would embed their new calendar on their website if they<a class=\"excerpt-read-more\" href=\"https://time.ly/hubs-can-leverage-free-beta-calendars/\" title=\"ReadHow Hubs Can Leverage Free Beta Calendars\">...</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly/hubs-can-leverage-free-beta-calendars/\">How Hubs Can Leverage Free Beta Calendars</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://time.ly\">Timely</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Finding Events In Your Area &#8211; Community Hubs</title>\n		<link>https://time.ly/finding-events-area-community-hubs/</link>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 18 Jan 2017 19:52:12 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kafui-hotsonyame]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Other Stuff]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://time.ly/?p=323057</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>You have an amazing looking calendar which is great! What are some ways in which you can keep your calendar relevant and full? 1. Pulling in feeds Save yourself some ti