017-01-22 22:22:07','2017-01-22 22:22:07','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-34\" src=\"http://vps188085.ovh.net/imdek/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/4x4_trial_sm2017.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"842\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Der Monkey Offroad Club lädt vom 21.-23. April 2017 alle Trial-, Geländewagen- und Quad/ATV-Fans nach Bürglen TG ein. Der 1. Lauf zur Schweizer Meisterschaft Geländewagentrial sowie der Schweizer Meisterschaft Quadtrial findet am Samstag 22.4.2017 statt. Zeitgleich findet auch eine kleine regionale Offroadmesse statt. Das Fahrerlager öffnet am Freitag, 21.4.2017 ab 15.00 Uhr.</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_H9sVDqfcjs','4×4 Trial SM2017 Strabag','','publish','open','closed','','4x4-trial-sm2017-strabag','','','2017-01-22 22:24:06','2017-01-22 22:24:06','',0,'http://vps188085.ovh.net/imdek/wp/?post_type=ai1ec_event&#038;p=33',0,'ai1ec_event','',0),(34,1,'2017-01-22 22:23:10','2017-01-22 22:23:10','','4x4_trial_sm2017','','inherit','open','closed','','4x4_trial_sm2017','','','2017-01-22 22:23:10','2017-01-22 22:23:10','',33,'http://vps188085.ovh.net/imdek/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/4x4_trial_sm2017.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(35,1,'2017-01-22 22:24:02','2017-01-22 22:24:02','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-34\" src=\"http://vps188085.ovh.net/imdek/wp/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/4x4_trial_sm2017.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"842\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Der Monkey Offroad Club lädt vom 21.-23. April 2017 alle Trial-, Geländewagen- und Quad/ATV-Fans nach Bürglen TG ein. Der 1. Lauf zur Schweizer Meisterschaft Geländewagentrial sowie der Schweizer Meisterschaft Quadtrial findet am Samstag 22.4.2017 statt. Zeitgleich findet auch eine kleine regionale Offroadmesse statt. Das Fahrerlager öffnet am Freitag, 21.4.2017 ab 15.00 Uhr.</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_H9sVDqfcjs','4×4 Trial SM2017 Strabag','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-autosave-v1','','','2017-01-22 22:24:02','2017-01-22 22:24:02','',33,'http://vps188085.ovh.net/imdek/wp/?p=35',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2017-01-22 22:53:15','2017-01-22 22:53:15','<em><strong>Organiser</strong></em>\r\n\r\nThe organiser of the <strong>17<sup>th</sup> Croatia Trophy</strong> is <strong>Croatia</strong><strong> Trophy Organizing Team</strong>. We’ve been present in Off-Road, nationally and internationally, for <strong>19</strong> years now.\r\nWe are very proud co-organizer of the Supersylvania Trophy-CROATIA 1998 and 1999.We are the organizer of Christmass Trophy 2002-2004 in Bregana, Croatia, as well as the one and only organizer of Croatia Trophy 2000 – 2017.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Registrtion &amp; payment</strong></em>\r\n\r\nOnline registration through our web site is preferable.\r\nAfter we receive your registration you will get official confirmation mail, your start number as well as an invoice with payment details.\r\nPlease remember your start number and present it by the registration in the Base Camp\r\nEntry fee for The “Croatia Trophy” has not been changed for 9 years (entry fee list is available on demand). ATV drivers participate as a single participant and therefore their entry fee is 50% less then car entry fee.\r\nAll participants who are going to make their registration and payment until the <strong>31<sup>st</sup> of January 2017</strong> are granted a <strong>10%</strong>-discount. Discount policy does not apply for catering prices for service/support team members.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>\r\nCrews, teams and classes</strong></em>\r\n\r\nEach vehicle has to be occupied by two persons (driver and co-driver). Both persons have to have a valid driving licence, and are free to exchange each other behind the steering wheel at any time.\r\nATV drivers register and participate as a single driver. They must be a member of ATV club and prove ATV driving experience to the Organizer.\r\nParticipants are divided in classes. Cars are divided in” Trophy” and “Adventure” class. ATV’s are separate class. They are also divided in” Trophy” and “Adventure” class. ATV’s that drive by the “Trophy Class” Road Book must for a team of two. Single ATV driver can drive only “Adventure Class” Road Book.\r\n\r\nThe difference between “Trophy” and “Adventure” class is in the road book. “Adventure Class” road book is not as demanding as “Trophy Class” road book.\r\n\r\n“Adventure Class” demands top driving skills by every participant.\r\n\r\nIt is not a Rally. It uses tracks of ”Croatia Trophy” but without most difficult parts and long winching areas.\r\nIt is not light class, it is not tourist class. It is ultimate adventure.\r\nIt is genuine off road, first of all.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Allowed vehicles</strong></em>\r\n\r\nEvery 4×4 vehicle that is road legal in its country of origin (has a registration plate and a valid international insurance certificate) is allowed to enter the race.\r\nVehicles with a weight-total over 3,5 t can’t participate in the event. Each vehicle has to have a firmly fixed winch. It must also be equipped with the following: trip master, seat-belts, linen straps for pull-outs (in case you should miss to use the tree-protection, you’d have to face the penalty and even disqualification), protective gloves, 2 helmets, first aid-box and fire-extinguisher. ATV drivers (who cannot have seat belts) will wear protective clothing.\r\nSpare wheel(s), appropriate car jack and mud anchor are strongly recommendable.\r\nWe advise you also to store some water, food, garbage-bags, personal things, and medicaments for personal use, tools and spare parts in your vehicle.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Roll cage is mandatory for all vehicles.</strong></em>\r\nTyres must be from serial production. No private workshops.\r\nTractor tyres are not allowed.\r\nGPS is not allowed.\r\nRadios are not allowed, except for the communication between driver and co-driver.\r\nGSM mobile phones are not allowed, except for the case of the emergency.\r\nWearing helmets and seat belts are mandatory while in stage.\r\nWearing protective gloves are mandatory when operating cable.\r\n<strong>Trophy Class\r\n</strong>Vehicles in ”Trophy Class” must have front and rear winch.\r\n<strong><em>Adventure Class\r\n</em></strong>Vehicles in “Adventure Class” must have front winch only. Rear winch is optional.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Vehicles with portal axels are not allowed in “Adventure Class”</strong></em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Camp/Service</strong></em>\r\n\r\nThere’s going to be catering service, car wash as well as a doctor at your disposal in the Camp. The camp is going to be supplied with fresh drinkable water, garbage containers, oil waste container and toilets. Electricity is not available but there will be possibility to purchase the wood. Cutting the wood outside the camp is strictly forbidden as well as illegal connections to the electric poles in the camp and private car wash (inside or outside the camp in the nearby rivers). There will be no fuel tanking possibilities in camp. Petrol station is 7 km from camp.\r\n\r\nThe towing service of the Trophy will pick up the broken vehicles along the track…and will bring you to the closest road accessible to your service team, if necessary.\r\nPrivate service-teams that have been registered in advance are allowed, but they can’t approach the racing track. We accept all kind of service/support vehicles except motocross bikes.\r\n\r\nWild camping is not allowed.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Catering</strong></em>\r\n\r\nThe catering consists of breakfast, lunch-package and dinner for 7 days plus winner’s celebration dinner. Bring your own plates, jugs and cutlery. Drinks are paid separately. Each member of service/support team is obliged to take catering. Due to the huge increase of food prices, the discount policy does not apply to catering service for service/support team members.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Road book</strong></em>\r\